long_desc.thetext:
While doing the transition from 0.7 to 0.8 I deleted all indexes and started the indexer from scratch. However, it exited in the middle of indexing.
This is what prstat says while the indexer is running:
PID USERNAME SIZE RSS STATE PRI NICE TIME CPU PROCESS/NLWP 7695 vk 309M 295M cpu1 48 0 0:13:17 36% java/16
The indexer was run from /usr/opengrok/bin/OpenGrok script.
When running the indexer again (incremental), it completed fine.
When discussing this with Lubos we determined that the indexer ran out of memory.
The other thing is that there was no warning message whatsoever - the logging level was set to SEVERE.
jvisualvm says the heap limit was 1G when running the indexing again.
Hence, the default memory limit should be increased.

Created attachment 3125 jvisualvm screenshot
this was after the indexer finished its incremental job

I added 2GB mx heap size by default into OpenGrok script in commit 912:e3b0f4566cfd
it would be nice if we could check whether this will fix the problem (meaning restarting the indexer in new instance base to see whether we hit the problem on the xen gate again ... )
Closing the bug since the fix went into 0.8.1. Please reopen if this is still an issue.
